estyle brand.</li><li><b>Price Range:</b> $50.00 USD - $380.00 USD</li><li><b>Where to Buy:</b> Available now on <a href="https://hbx.com/men/brands/dime">HBX</a></li></ul><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/new-arrivals-from-hbx-dime" title="New Arrivals From HBX: Dime" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=38880" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=38880" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2Ftshirt-3-1-6d2c5_1765511642.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1347	1131	Action Figures: Antonio Corrales Is Following His Own Blueprint With Corrupt Kid	action-figures-antonio-corrales-is-following-his-own-blueprint-with-corrupt-kid	published	2025-12-11 23:07:53+00	3	17	\N	Action Figures, created in partnership with DraftKings, is a content series spotlighting the people who believe in what's next and make every move count. From athletes, creators, and innovators rew...	Action Figures: Antonio Corrales Is Following His Own Blueprint With Corrupt Kid	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F09%2Faction-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>Action Figures, created in partnership with DraftKings, is a content series spotlighting the people who believe in what's next and make every move count. From athletes, creators, and innovators rewriting the playbook, these voices are united in a shared mindset: a commitment to hustle and to ignite their passion on every play. For the third installment, Action Figures highlights Antonio Corrales, the founder and designer of Corrupt Kid, a fashion label rewriting the blueprint on custom-made, utility-driven streetwear.When we meet up with Corrales, he's busy at work in the studio. Growing up in Worcester, Massachusetts, Corrales never intended to leave his hometown, despite his dream of becoming a fashion designer. The calling came at a young age, watching his grandmother sew and tailor garments at home. She taught him how to use traditional machinery and fabrication tools, and while studying at Bentley University, he began creating his own designs."I would take things apart, put them back together, distress them, and it quickly became an obsession," he recalls. "I would spend maybe a minimum of 12 hours a day just sewing, and I eventually taught myself how to make clothes from scratch and create pattern drafts. Now, every day is a challenge to learn something new."Reimagining the BlueprintSelf-taught and self-inspired, Corrales' design philosophy is simple: he makes clothes that he wants to wear. He's bound to collections that are rugged yet expertly tailored, with a knack for reconstructing denim. "My inspirations come from vintage, old-school military and tactical uniforms, farm wear, even corporate workwear. I love jeans — that's my main specialty. I see how I can tweak the seams, button fly, or add utility pockets to a pair of denim that no one's seen before."The Power of LeadershipCorrales' fashion imprint, Corrupt Kid, founded in 2021, specializes in street-inspired garments with strong military and utilitarian elements — distressed, baggy, patchwork and upcycled designs that combine these sensibilities into an edgy visual language. In a league of his own, what motivates Corrales is protecting his sense of authorship and innovation, but he's quick to point out that no one propels to the top without the help of others. Before launching his brand, he was an avid soccer player and distinctly remembers the teachings his coach imparted. "Learning how to lead a team and accomplish your goals together is very similar to running a campaign or designing a collection. I have to delegate tasks to different members of the team and encourage us all to stay focused on a shared goal." He mentions that he'd like to design a custom kit for his local team, the New England Revolution, but in the meantime, he's busy fulfilling orders for artists like Kendrick Lamar.Finding Your TribeWhen Lamar's team reached out to secure custom garments for the artist's 2025 Grand National Tour, Corrales immediately gravitated to Lamar's vision. "The main focus was referencing baggy clothes from the '90s, that classic LA, Compton look, and mixing that with military elements. I was like, 'Perfect, I can do that.' I stuck to my roots." A wordsmith from a mad city, Lamar, was clad in baggy denim with patchwork camo overlays and oversized pockets — ensembles that perfectly encapsulated the artist's energy while highlighting Corrupt Kid's distinct design ethos.Since then, Corrales has hosted various pop-ups with upcoming activations slated for 2026 in Boston, Austin, and Cambridge. He's secured stock deals with brands in Osaka, Japan, and is hungry to continue growing his brand. Expanding the bounds of his creativity and the future of Corrupt Kid, he's gearing up for his first runway collection for Fall 2026. "I'm challenging myself to create a 15-20 piece collection. Formal wear is a huge challenge for me that I want to begin exploring. We're working on button-ups, blazer jackets, trench coats, denim, and even looking at creating a pair of boots."Action Figures Close to HomeWhen asked if there have been action figures in his life who've influenced his professional development, Corrales has no idols in mind aside from his father. "My father is a huge action figure of mine. He came to this country when he was eight years old without speaking English. He jumped into school as a first-generation college [student]. He's really where I got my work ethic from, and he inspires me every day to keep going."Inspired by family members and fashion elements that illuminate working class communities, Corrales has big dreams that are rooted close to home. His aspirations align with a hustler mentality, to learn, grow, and pick up the pieces when things require more effort and time than expected. But this journey is part of the magic, and it’s a sentiment deeply embedded in Corrupt Kid — breaking the paradigm starts with building the pattern of loose parts.Dive into the Action Figure journeys of Round21 founder, Jasmine Maietta, and Barriers Worldwide founder, Steven Barter, spotlighted by DraftKings here.</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video" title="Action Figures: Antonio Corrales Is Following His Own Blueprint With Corrupt Kid" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.431+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.431+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.434+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.434+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F09%2Faction-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><br></br></p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/draftkings-action-figures" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Action Figures</a>, created in partnership with <a href="https://www.draftkings.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">DraftKings</a>, is a content series spotlighting the people who believe in what's next and make every move count. From athletes, creators, and innovators rewriting the playbook, these voices are united in a shared mindset: a commitment to hustle and to ignite their passion on every play. For the third installment, Action Figures highlights Antonio Corrales, the founder and designer of <a href="https://www.instagram.com/corruptkid/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Corrupt Kid</a>, a fashion label rewriting the blueprint on custom-made, utility-driven streetwear.</p><p><br></br><br /><center><iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1145235572?h=a458f06860&amp;badge=0&amp;autopause=0&autoplay=1&muted=1" width="640" height="1138" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe></center><br /><br></br></p><p>When we meet up with Corrales, he's busy at work in the studio. Growing up in Worcester, Massachusetts, Corrales never intended to leave his hometown, despite his dream of becoming a fashion designer. The calling came at a young age, watching his grandmother sew and tailor garments at home. She taught him how to use traditional machinery and fabrication tools, and while studying at Bentley University, he began creating his own designs.<br /><br></br><br />"I would take things apart, put them back together, distress them, and it quickly became an obsession," he recalls. "I would spend maybe a minimum of 12 hours a day just sewing, and I eventually taught myself how to make clothes from scratch and create pattern drafts. Now, every day is a challenge to learn something new."</p><p><br></br></p><p><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-2.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-3.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-4.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-5.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /></p><p><br></br></p><p><center><br /><h2>Reimagining the Blueprint</h2><p></center><br /><br></br><br />Self-taught and self-inspired, Corrales' design philosophy is simple: he makes clothes that he wants to wear. He's bound to collections that are rugged yet expertly tailored, with a knack for reconstructing denim. "My inspirations come from vintage, old-school military and tactical uniforms, farm wear, even corporate workwear. I love jeans — that's my main specialty. I see how I can tweak the seams, button fly, or add utility pockets to a pair of denim that no one's seen before."</p><p><br></br></p><div style="position: relative;"><img style="max-width: none; width: 100%;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-6.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /></div><p><br></br></p><p><center><br /><h2>The Power of Leadership</h2><p></center><br /><br></br><br />Corrales' fashion imprint, <a href="https://corruptkid.com/?utm_source=ig&utm_medium=social&utm_content=link_in_bio&fbclid=PAZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQMMjU2MjgxMDQwNTU4AAGnwh7vUx-7A32Hi3qOVhnKIyyM2ywyOhUQRnh2LXTzliwHNLh-NXIARLoBbYY_aem_UoC5Co07SlvTc5lmrdxkXA" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Corrupt Kid</a>, founded in 2021, specializes in street-inspired garments with strong military and utilitarian elements — distressed, baggy, patchwork and upcycled designs that combine these sensibilities into an edgy visual language. In a league of his own, what motivates Corrales is protecting his sense of authorship and innovation, but he's quick to point out that no one propels to the top without the help of others. Before launching his brand, he was an avid soccer player and distinctly remembers the teachings his coach imparted. "Learning how to lead a team and accomplish your goals together is very similar to running a campaign or designing a collection. I have to delegate tasks to different members of the team and encourage us all to stay focused on a shared goal." He mentions that he'd like to design a custom kit for his local team, the New England Revolution, but in the meantime, he's busy fulfilling orders for artists like <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/Kendrick-Lamar" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Kendrick Lamar</a>.</p><p><br></br></p><p><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-7.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-8.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-9.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-10.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /><img style="max-width: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-11.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /></p><p><br></br></p><p><center><br /><h2>Finding Your Tribe</h2><p></center><br /><br></br><br />When Lamar's team reached out to secure custom garments for the artist's 2025 Grand National Tour, Corrales immediately gravitated to Lamar's vision. "The main focus was referencing baggy clothes from the '90s, that classic LA, Compton look, and mixing that with military elements. I was like, 'Perfect, I can do that.' I stuck to my roots." A wordsmith from a mad city, Lamar, was clad in baggy denim with patchwork camo overlays and oversized pockets — ensembles that perfectly encapsulated the artist's energy while highlighting Corrupt Kid's distinct design ethos.</p><p><br></br></p><div style="position: relative;"><img style="max-width: none; width: 100%;" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-12.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /></div><p><br></br></p><p>Since then, Corrales has hosted various pop-ups with upcoming activations slated for 2026 in Boston, Austin, and Cambridge. He's secured stock deals with brands in Osaka, Japan, and is hungry to continue growing his brand. Expanding the bounds of his creativity and the future of Corrupt Kid, he's gearing up for his first runway collection for Fall 2026. "I'm challenging myself to create a 15-20 piece collection. Formal wear is a huge challenge for me that I want to begin exploring. We're working on button-ups, blazer jackets, trench coats, denim, and even looking at creating a pair of boots."</p><p><center><br /><h2>Action Figures Close to Home</h2><p></center><br /><br></br><br />When asked if there have been action figures in his life who've influenced his professional development, Corrales has no idols in mind aside from his father. "My father is a huge action figure of mine. He came to this country when he was eight years old without speaking English. He jumped into school as a first-generation college [student]. He's really where I got my work ethic from, and he inspires me every day to keep going."</p><p><br></br><br /><center><img class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-13.png" alt="DraftKings Action Figures Antonio Corrales Corruptkid Fashion Label Kendrick Lamar " /></center><br /><br></br></p><p>Inspired by family members and fashion elements that illuminate working class communities, Corrales has big dreams that are rooted close to home. His aspirations align with a hustler mentality, to learn, grow, and pick up the pieces when things require more effort and time than expected. But this journey is part of the magic, and it’s a sentiment deeply embedded in Corrupt Kid — breaking the paradigm starts with building the pattern of loose parts.<br /><br></br><br />Dive into the <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/draftkings-action-figures" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Action Figure</a> journeys of Round21 founder, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/weareround21" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Jasmine Maietta</a>, and Barriers Worldwide founder, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/barterbarter/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Steven Barter</a>, spotlighted by DraftKings <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/draftkings-action-figures" rel="noopener" target="_blank">here</a>. </p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/action-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video" title="Action Figures: Antonio Corrales Is Following His Own Blueprint With Corrupt Kid" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=55846" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=55846" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F09%2Faction-figures-draftkings-antonio-corrales-artist-interview-series-video-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1340	1124	Oakley Brings Teeth Alpha Back In New Collab With Podpah	oakley-brings-teeth-alpha-back-in-new-collab-with-podpah	published	2025-12-12 15:14:50+00	3	17	\N	SummaryOakley and Podpah launched their second collaboration across eyewear, apparel, and footwear, following the rapid sell-out success of their initial release.The collection is highlighted by a...	Oakley Brings Teeth Alpha Back In New Collab With Podpah	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F12%2Foakley-teeth-alpha-podpah-second-collaboration-brazil-release-info-0.png?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&format=png&fit=max" /></p><div>SummaryOakley and Podpah launched their second collaboration across eyewear, apparel, and footwear, following the rapid sell-out success of their initial release.The collection is highlighted by a limited-edition Plantaris eyewear model with interchangeable lenses, and an exclusive reinterpretation of the iconic Teeth Alpha sneaker.The collaboration merges Oakley’s performance heritage with the podcast's substantial cultural reach and focus on authentic representation for the Brazilian youth market.Following the record-breaking sales of their initial release, which sold out in just two minutes, Oakley and Podpah, Brazil’s highly influential podcast, have launched their second collaborative collection. The partnership, which expands into eyewear, apparel, and footwear, merges Oakley’s performance legacy with the substantial cultural reach of Podpah. The podcast, hosted by founders Igão and Mítico, functions as a significant platform for urban culture and youth engagement in Brazil, positioning the hosts as key cultural representatives.The accompanying campaign, titled “Between Two Worlds,” explores the concept of duality in the hosts’ lives, the constant intersection of "chaos and calm." Starring Igão and Mítico, the visual content tracks their daily routines, using a shifting soundtrack to underscore the blend of high-energy professional moments and a forward-looking brand vision. The new collection features key models designed for versatility. The Plantaris eyewear has been released in a limited-edition format with light gray frames, distinguished by the inclusion of two sets of interchangeable lenses. The apparel selection includes two new t-shirts, one featuring the brand's symbolic Medusa figure and the other incorporating double-stripes to reflect an athletic inspiration. Additionally, the iconic Teeth Alpha footwear model has been reinterpreted in an exclusive black colorway with a white sole.The second Oakley x Podpah collaboration is set to further the successful synergy between the brands by building a sustained creative narrative focused on authenticity and representativeness, available in Oakley's stores in Brazil.</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/oakley-teeth-alpha-podpah-second-collaboration-brazil-release-info" title="Oakley Brings Teeth Alpha Back In New Collab With Podpah" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.332+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.332+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.335+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.335+00	f	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F12%2Foakley-teeth-alpha-podpah-second-collaboration-brazil-release-info-0.png?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&format=png&fit=max" /></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><ul><li>Oakley and Podpah launched their second collaboration across eyewear, apparel, and footwear, following the rapid sell-out success of their initial release.</li><li>The collection is highlighted by a limited-edition Plantaris eyewear model with interchangeable lenses, and an exclusive reinterpretation of the iconic Teeth Alpha sneaker.</li><li>The collaboration merges Oakley’s performance heritage with the podcast's substantial cultural reach and focus on authentic representation for the Brazilian youth market.</li></ul><p>Following the record-breaking sales of their initial release, which sold out in just two minutes, <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/oakley" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Oakley</a> and <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/podpah" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Podpah</a>, Brazil’s highly influential podcast, have launched their second collaborative collection. </p><p>The partnership, which expands into eyewear, apparel, and footwear, merges Oakley’s performance legacy with the substantial cultural reach of Podpah. The podcast, hosted by founders Igão and Mítico, functions as a significant platform for urban culture and youth engagement in Brazil, positioning the hosts as key cultural representatives.</p><p>The accompanying campaign, titled “Between Two Worlds,” explores the concept of duality in the hosts’ lives, the constant intersection of "chaos and calm." Starring Igão and Mítico, the visual content tracks their daily routines, using a shifting soundtrack to underscore the blend of high-energy professional moments and a forward-looking brand vision. </p><p>The new collection features key models designed for versatility. The Plantaris eyewear has been released in a limited-edition format with light gray frames, distinguished by the inclusion of two sets of interchangeable lenses. </p><p>The apparel selection includes two new t-shirts, one featuring the brand's symbolic Medusa figure and the other incorporating double-stripes to reflect an athletic inspiration. Additionally, the iconic Teeth Alpha footwear model has been reinterpreted in an exclusive black colorway with a white sole.</p><p>The second Oakley x Podpah collaboration is set to further the successful synergy between the brands by building a sustained creative narrative focused on authenticity and representativeness, available in Oakley's stores in Brazil.</p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/oakley-teeth-alpha-podpah-second-collaboration-brazil-release-info" title="Oakley Brings Teeth Alpha Back In New Collab With Podpah" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=43191" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=43191" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F12%2Foakley-teeth-alpha-podpah-second-collaboration-brazil-release-info-0.png?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&format=png&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1349	1133	Matt McCormick's Austin Post Collection Embodies the Mythology of the Cowboy	matt-mccormick-s-austin-post-collection-embodies-the-mythology-of-the-cowboy	published	2025-12-10 21:45:33+00	3	17	\N	Post Malone's eponymous brand, Austin Post, and Los Angeles-based artist Matt McCormick have co-designed a capsule centered around their shared exploration of Western iconography. In an exclusive i...	Matt McCormick's Austin Post Collection Embodies the Mythology of the Cowboy	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F10%2Faustin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>Post Malone's eponymous brand, Austin Post, and Los Angeles-based artist Matt McCormick have co-designed a capsule centered around their shared exploration of Western iconography. In an exclusive interview with Hypebeast, McCormick expands on the works that inspired their limited-edition collection, placing a particular focus on the quintessentially American mythology of the cowboy.Marking Austin Post's inaugural installment of the Studio Series, the artist's limited-edition capsule is part of an ongoing initiative powered by artists and cultural figures whose work aligns with the brand's vision.Indeed, the musician-turned-designer's aesthetic and McCormick's practice approach similar themes. McCormick's mixture of various mediums and styles, exploring American archetypes with a Western sensibility, runs parallel to both Post Malone's music and his recently launched label.For instance, take McCormick's Ceremony Of Certainty: Featuring a discolored inkjet desert landscape superimposed with a hand-drawn charcoal cowboy illustration, the artist shared that he aimed to "create a push and pull between the more modern technique of inkjet printing and the classic charcoal drawing style.""When I started making that work, I was really interested in using failing printers to make images with an almost roll of the dice mentality. There was something that would happen with the colors and textures of the backgrounds when run continuously through the old printers that would create a really interesting moment visually," McCormick shared.The tensions between the modern and classic, as well as the digital and human-made, are palpable not only in Post Malone's sonic fusion of 808-powered hip-hop with Americana folk rock, but also in his brand's juxtaposition of minimalist streetwear with Western classics like check shirting and suede trucker jackets.For the new release, the partners have revealed five silhouettes in varied colorways, including tees, a hoodie, and a crewneck sweater, each featuring graphics based on the artist's work. At the front of each garment, a discreet “At First Light — Season One” typographic print nods to the brand's FW25 debut, while the back is emblazoned with McCormick's artwork."It was really about getting the pieces to embody the same process that I used when making the original works."This isn't McCormick's first rodeo in fashion. Ten years ago, the artist launched his own brand, One of These Days, translating his visual language directly into ready-to-wear garments. "I’m no stranger to the process, but what was so great about working with Austin Post is that they really wanted to treat the art as art and not as a graphic, which was highly refreshing," he said. "It was really about getting the pieces to embody the same process that I used when making the original works."Furthermore, Post Malone isn't the first musician McCormick has collaborated with. His artwork has been used for album covers by a diverse range of artists — from Puerto Rican pop star Bad Bunny to rapper Don Toliver and country singer Zach Bryan. "Music is central to my existence. It’s always playing and always dictating my mood," he shared. "Working with musicians has been such a gift because it has been a small way that I can be a part of that conversation. Almost every moment for me is carried along by music in some way," he added.Like McCormick's pieces, Post Malone's discography has unfolded in a dialogue of contrasts. His breakout 2015 single "White Iverson" was a viral R&amp;B/hip-hop track, which debuted on Soundcloud with auto-tuned vocals and a minimal trap production. Almost a decade later, the sound of his 2024 LP F-1 Trillion was starkly different — a definitively country album featuring collaborators like Dolly Parton and Tim McGraw. At this stage in his career as both a musician and designer, Post Malone certainly embodies a contemporary facet of the rugged cowboy character.For McCormick, the cowboy represents far more than romantic nostalgia or a superficial aesthetic. Instead, he understands it as a global "symbol of Americanism," and an allegory for modern masculinity. However, rather than advancing any particular interpretation, McCormick prefers to "place seemingly incompatible or different cultural touch points together to create a dialogue that may not have happened otherwise.""It’s not that difficult to put on the costume and at least for a moment pretend that you embody the mythology of the character."In addition to Ceremony of Certainty, McCormick debuts Among the Low Light as another featured graphic. The development of the piece was "a way to treat the cowboy image as an almost faded memory of the past."Aiming to broaden the scope of his style, McCormick made an effort to mirror the effect of a screen print by hand-painting his canvases. As part of the ongoing series, he created a faded patina through a meticulous process, "slowly building the colors up by rubbing paint into the canvas over and over with a rag and a mix of paint and paint thinner."As one could easily gather from the paintings and paraphernalia in his studio, the cowboy is an ever-present character in McCormick's world. He reckons that the archetype has endured for so many decades because it has offered a consistent "visual representation of America," likening it to "a can of Coke, cherry pie, or Ford truck."However, he points out that "the major difference from these objects is that it is very easy for one to imagine themselves or see themselves in the cowboy." "It’s not that difficult to put on the costume and at least for a moment pretend that you embody the mythology of the character."The Matt McCormick x Austin Post collection is set for release on Thursday, December 11, at 8 AM PT/11 AM ET exclusively on austin-Post.com.</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info" title="Matt McCormick&#039;s Austin Post Collection Embodies the Mythology of the Cowboy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.461+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.461+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.465+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.465+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F10%2Faustin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/post-malone">Post Malone</a>'s eponymous brand, <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/austin-post">Austin Post</a>, and Los Angeles-based artist <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/matt-mccormick">Matt McCormick</a> have co-designed a capsule centered around their shared exploration of Western iconography. In an exclusive interview with Hypebeast, McCormick expands on the works that inspired their limited-edition collection, placing a particular focus on the quintessentially American mythology of the cowboy.</p><p>Marking Austin Post's inaugural installment of the <em>Studio Series</em>, the artist's limited-edition capsule is part of an ongoing initiative powered by artists and cultural figures whose work aligns with the brand's vision.</p><p>Indeed, the musician-turned-designer's aesthetic and McCormick's practice approach similar themes. McCormick's mixture of various mediums and styles, exploring American archetypes with a Western sensibility, runs parallel to both Post Malone's music and his recently launched label.</p><p><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-20.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-18.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-23.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-21.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-26.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-24.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-29.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-27.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-32.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-30.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-35.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-33.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-38.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-36.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-39.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-41.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-44.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-42.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-47.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-45.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-50.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-48.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-53.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-51.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-56.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-54.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-59.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-57.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-62.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-60.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-65.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-63.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-66.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-68.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-71.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-69.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /></p><p>For instance, take McCormick's <em>Ceremony Of Certainty</em>: Featuring a discolored inkjet desert landscape superimposed with a hand-drawn charcoal cowboy illustration, the artist shared that he aimed to "create a push and pull between the more modern technique of inkjet printing and the classic charcoal drawing style."</p><p>"When I started making that work, I was really interested in using failing printers to make images with an almost roll of the dice mentality. There was something that would happen with the colors and textures of the backgrounds when run continuously through the old printers that would create a really interesting moment visually," McCormick shared.</p><p>The tensions between the modern and classic, as well as the digital and human-made, are palpable not only in Post Malone's sonic fusion of 808-powered hip-hop with Americana folk rock, but also in his brand's juxtaposition of minimalist streetwear with Western classics like check shirting and suede trucker jackets.</p><p>For the new release, the partners have revealed five silhouettes in varied colorways, including tees, a hoodie, and a crewneck sweater, each featuring graphics based on the artist's work. At the front of each garment, a discreet “At First Light — Season One” typographic print nods to the brand's FW25 debut, while the back is emblazoned with McCormick's artwork.</p><p><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-17.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-16.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-7.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /></p><p><q>"It was really about getting the pieces to embody the same process that I used when making the original works."</q></p><p>This isn't McCormick's first rodeo in fashion. Ten years ago, the artist launched his own brand, <a href="https://oneofthesedays.com/?srsltid=AfmBOor3fL-KJUS-aI4RbuZDrv4U6P3UqBm9XRA9q2VPB0C_oonxPjZp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One of These Days</a>, translating his visual language directly into ready-to-wear garments. "I’m no stranger to the process, but what was so great about working with Austin Post is that they really wanted to treat the art as art and not as a graphic, which was highly refreshing," he said. "It was really about getting the pieces to embody the same process that I used when making the original works."</p><p>Furthermore, Post Malone isn't the first musician McCormick has collaborated with. His artwork has been used for album covers by a diverse range of artists — from Puerto Rican pop star <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/bad-bunny">Bad Bunny</a> to rapper <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/don-toliver">Don Toliver</a> and country singer <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/zach-bryan">Zach Bryan</a>. "Music is central to my existence. It’s always playing and always dictating my mood," he shared. "Working with musicians has been such a gift because it has been a small way that I can be a part of that conversation. Almost every moment for me is carried along by music in some way," he added.</p><p>Like McCormick's pieces, Post Malone's discography has unfolded in a dialogue of contrasts. His breakout 2015 single "White Iverson" was a viral R&amp;B/hip-hop track, which debuted on Soundcloud with auto-tuned vocals and a minimal trap production. Almost a decade later, the sound of his 2024 LP <em>F-1 Trillion</em> was starkly different — a definitively country album featuring collaborators like <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/dolly-parton">Dolly Parton</a> and <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/tim-mcgraw">Tim McGraw</a>. At this stage in his career as both a musician and designer, Post Malone certainly embodies a contemporary facet of the rugged cowboy character.</p><p>For McCormick, the cowboy represents far more than romantic nostalgia or a superficial aesthetic. Instead, he understands it as a global "symbol of Americanism," and an allegory for modern masculinity. However, rather than advancing any particular interpretation, McCormick prefers to "place seemingly incompatible or different cultural touch points together to create a dialogue that may not have happened otherwise."</p><p><q>"It’s not that difficult to put on the costume and at least for a moment pretend that you embody the mythology of the character."</q></p><p><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-2.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-4.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-3.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-1.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-10.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-13.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /><br /><img src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/10/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-15.jpg" alt="Matt McCormick Austin Post Collection Interview" /></p><p>In addition to <em>Ceremony of Certainty</em>, McCormick debuts <em>Among the Low Light</em> as another featured graphic. The development of the piece was "a way to treat the cowboy image as an almost faded memory of the past."</p><p>Aiming to broaden the scope of his style, McCormick made an effort to mirror the effect of a screen print by hand-painting his canvases. As part of the ongoing series, he created a faded patina through a meticulous process, "slowly building the colors up by rubbing paint into the canvas over and over with a rag and a mix of paint and paint thinner."</p><p>As one could easily gather from the paintings and paraphernalia in his studio, the cowboy is an ever-present character in McCormick's world. He reckons that the archetype has endured for so many decades because it has offered a consistent "visual representation of America," likening it to "a can of Coke, cherry pie, or Ford truck."</p><p>However, he points out that "the major difference from these objects is that it is very easy for one to imagine themselves or see themselves in the cowboy." "It’s not that difficult to put on the costume and at least for a moment pretend that you embody the mythology of the character."</p><p>The Matt McCormick x Austin Post collection is set for release on Thursday, December 11, at 8 AM PT/11 AM ET exclusively on austin-Post.com.</p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/austin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info" title="Matt McCormick&#039;s Austin Post Collection Embodies the Mythology of the Cowboy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=43871" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=43871" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F10%2Faustin-post-x-matt-mccormick-collaboration-collection-release-info-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1350	1134	BAPE Opens Its First‑Ever All‑White Concept Store & Café at Hong Kong’s 1881 Heritage	bape-opens-its-first-ever-all-white-concept-store-cafe-at-hong-kong-s-1881-heritage	published	2025-12-11 10:31:19+00	3	17	\N	SummaryBAPE opened its first all-white concept store at 1881 Heritage, Hong KongThe location also introduces the BAPE CAFE!?, marking the brand's first full-service dining concept in the cityThe st...	BAPE Opens Its First‑Ever All‑White Concept Store & Café at Hong Kong’s 1881 Heritage	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fbape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>SummaryBAPE opened its first all-white concept store at 1881 Heritage, Hong KongThe location also introduces the BAPE CAFE!?, marking the brand's first full-service dining concept in the cityThe store opened on October 25, but the café will unveil December 12BAPE has inaugurated a landmark retail space in Hong Kong, unveiling its first-ever all-white concept store and café at the historic 1881 Heritage in Tsim Sha Tsui. This new space signifies a bold evolution of the brand's retail identity, consciously departing from its traditional, vibrant camouflage aesthetic. The two-floor store occupies a prominent position within the main building, respectfully integrating its contemporary design with the site’s colonial architecture.The interior design executes a dramatic shift, utilizing a pristine, minimalist all-white color palette across both floors. This stark, monochromatic approach provides a fresh, gallery-like backdrop that intentionally highlights luxury materials, detailed craftsmanship and allows BAPE's colorful products to shine. Featuring white marble and premium finishes, the aesthetic successfully contrasts BAPE’s street origins with a refined, high-end architectural vision.The introduction of the BAPE CAFE!? on the first floor is a unique feature for this Hong Kong location. The café, accessed via an exclusive white marble staircase, mirrors the store's simplicity with a sleek, minimalist all-white interior that maximizes light and space. This venture marks BAPE’s first full-service dining concept within a Hong Kong store. Produced by FLIPPER'S, a popular Japanese chain known for their uber fluffy soufflé pancakes, the BAPE CAFE!? offers gourmet coffees, exclusive BAPE-themed dishes and bespoke beverages, ensuring the brand's presence extends into high-end hospitality and solidifying the store as a cultural destination.To commemorate the launch, BAPE released a limited-edition collection exclusive to the 1881 Heritage store, embracing the white theme. The BAPE STORE® 1881 HERITAGE officially opened its doors on October 25, 2025, with the café set to unveil on December 12.BAPE STORE® &amp; BAPE CAFÉ!?® produced by FLIPPER’S 1881 HERITAGEShop G08a &amp; G08b, Street level, 1881 Heritage,2A Canton Road, Tsim Sha Tsui,Kowloon, Hong Kong</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info" title="BAPE Opens Its First‑Ever All‑White Concept Store &amp; Café at Hong Kong’s 1881 Heritage" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.477+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.477+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.479+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.479+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fbape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><ul><li>BAPE opened its first all-white concept store at 1881 Heritage, Hong Kong</li><li>The location also introduces the BAPE CAFE!?, marking the brand's first full-service dining concept in the city</li><li>The store opened on October 25, but the café will unveil December 12</li></ul><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/bape" rel="noopener" target="_blank">BAPE</a> has inaugurated a landmark retail space in <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/hong-kong" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Hong Kong</a>, unveiling its first-ever all-white concept store and café at the historic 1881 Heritage in Tsim Sha Tsui. This new space signifies a bold evolution of the brand's retail identity, consciously departing from its traditional, vibrant camouflage aesthetic. The two-floor store occupies a prominent position within the main building, respectfully integrating its contemporary design with the site’s colonial architecture.</p><p>The interior design executes a dramatic shift, utilizing a pristine, minimalist all-white color palette across both floors. This stark, monochromatic approach provides a fresh, gallery-like backdrop that intentionally highlights luxury materials, detailed craftsmanship and allows BAPE's colorful products to shine. Featuring white marble and premium finishes, the aesthetic successfully contrasts BAPE’s street origins with a refined, high-end architectural vision.</p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-011.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-012.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-013.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-014.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-008.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-009.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-010.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-022.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-021.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-017.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-018.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-019.jpg" /></p><p><img alt="BAPE First All-White Concept Store & Cafe 1881 Heritage Hong Kong Opening Info" class="portrait" src="https://hypebeast.com/image/2025/12/11/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-020.jpg" /></p><p>The introduction of the BAPE CAFE!? on the first floor is a unique feature for this Hong Kong location. The café, accessed via an exclusive white marble staircase, mirrors the store's simplicity with a sleek, minimalist all-white interior that maximizes light and space. This venture marks BAPE’s first full-service dining concept within a Hong Kong store. Produced by FLIPPER'S, a popular Japanese chain known for their uber fluffy soufflé pancakes, the BAPE CAFE!? offers gourmet coffees, exclusive BAPE-themed dishes and bespoke beverages, ensuring the brand's presence extends into high-end hospitality and solidifying the store as a cultural destination.</p><p>To commemorate the launch, BAPE released a limited-edition collection exclusive to the 1881 Heritage store, embracing the white theme. The BAPE STORE® 1881 HERITAGE officially opened its doors on October 25, 2025, with the café set to unveil on December 12.</p><p><strong>BAPE STORE® &amp; BAPE CAFÉ!?® produced by FLIPPER’S 1881 HERITAGE</strong><br />Shop G08a &amp; G08b, Street level, 1881 Heritage,<br />2A Canton Road, Tsim Sha Tsui,<br />Kowloon, Hong Kong</p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/bape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info" title="BAPE Opens Its First‑Ever All‑White Concept Store &amp; Café at Hong Kong’s 1881 Heritage" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=45601" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=45601" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fbape-first-all-white-concept-store-cafe-1881-heritage-hong-kong-opening-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1351	1135	KITH TREATS Unveils Collaboration with Kellogg's Frosted Flakes and Tony the Tiger	kith-treats-unveils-collaboration-with-kellogg-s-frosted-flakes-and-tony-the-tiger	published	2025-12-11 09:59:10+00	3	17	\N	SummaryKITH TREATS collaborated with Kellogg's Frosted Flakes, featuring Tony the TigerThe collection includes apparel, housewares, and accessories with vintage brandingThe capsule drops on Decembe...	KITH TREATS Unveils Collaboration with Kellogg's Frosted Flakes and Tony the Tiger	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fkith-treat-kelloggs-frosted-flakes-cereal-tony-the-tiger-collaboration-collection-release-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>SummaryKITH TREATS collaborated with Kellogg's Frosted Flakes, featuring Tony the TigerThe collection includes apparel, housewares, and accessories with vintage brandingThe capsule drops on December 12 on KITH's website and in select storesCelebrating the holiday season, KITH TREATS has unveiled a collaboration with Kellogg's Frosted Flakes Cereal, featuring the iconic Tony the Tiger. With its range of playfully designed items, this collection is a heartfelt tribute to the beloved cereal brand.The collection consists of a series of apparel, including racing jackets, fleeces, hooded and crewneck heavyweights, graphic tees, and co-branded headwear. Furthermore, the collaboration extends to housewares, such as tablewares, and personal accessories. A standout item in the collection is undoubtedly the scarf, which cleverly mimics the distinctive scarf worn by Tony the Tiger. Every piece from the collection is seamlessly integrated with vintage and modern Kellogg's Frosted Flakes iconography, classic Tony the Tiger graphics, and Kith's signature collaborative logo.Alongside the launch of the collaboration, an animated advertisement has also been released. It stars Tony the Tiger and humorously features Ronnie Fieg as a staff member of a KITH TREATS store. The KITH TREATS for Kellogg's Frosted Flakes Cereal &amp; Tony the Tiger capsule collection will be available starting December 12 on KITH’s website and at all U.S. locations, as well as in Toronto. Check out the animation below.Kith Treats for Kellogg’s Frosted Flakes® Cereal &amp; Tony the Tiger® pic.twitter.com/XPvePCPWDY— Ronnie Fieg (@RonnieFieg) December 8, 2025</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/kith-treat-kelloggs-frosted-flakes-cereal-tony-the-tiger-collaboration-collection-release-info" title="KITH TREATS Unveils Collaboration with Kellogg&#039;s Frosted Flakes and Tony the Tiger" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.49+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.49+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.492+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.492+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fkith-treat-kelloggs-frosted-flakes-cereal-tony-the-tiger-collaboration-collection-release-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><ul><li>KITH TREATS collaborated with Kellogg's Frosted Flakes, featuring Tony the Tiger</li><li>The collection includes apparel, housewares, and accessories with vintage branding</li><li>The capsule drops on December 12 on KITH's website and in select stores</li></ul><p>Celebrating the holiday season, <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/kith">KITH</a> <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/kith-treats">TREATS</a> has unveiled a collaboration with <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/kellogg">Kellogg</a>'s Frosted Flakes Cereal, featuring the iconic <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/tony-the-tiger">Tony the Tiger</a>. With its range of playfully designed items, this collection is a heartfelt tribute to the beloved cereal brand.</p><p>The collection consists of a series of apparel, including racing jackets, fleeces, hooded and crewneck heavyweights, graphic tees, and co-branded headwear. Furthermore, the collaboration extends to housewares, such as tablewares, and personal accessories. A standout item in the collection is undoubtedly the scarf, which cleverly mimics the distinctive scarf worn by Tony the Tiger. Every piece from the collection is seamlessly integrated with vintage and modern Kellogg's Frosted Flakes iconography, classic Tony the Tiger graphics, and Kith's signature collaborative logo.</p><p>Alongside the launch of the collaboration, an animated advertisement has also been released. It stars Tony the Tiger and humorously features Ronnie Fieg as a staff member of a KITH TREATS store. The KITH TREATS for Kellogg's Frosted Flakes Cereal &amp; Tony the Tiger capsule collection will be available starting December 12 on <a href="http://kith.com">KITH’s website</a> and at all U.S. locations, as well as in Toronto. Check out the animation below.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Kith Treats for Kellogg’s Frosted Flakes® Cereal &amp; Tony the Tiger® <a href="https://t.co/XPvePCPWDY">pic.twitter.com/XPvePCPWDY</a></p><p>— Ronnie Fieg (@RonnieFieg) <a href="https://twitter.com/RonnieFieg/status/1998031094369939649?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">December 8, 2025</a></p></blockquote><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/kith-treat-kelloggs-frosted-flakes-cereal-tony-the-tiger-collaboration-collection-release-info" title="KITH TREATS Unveils Collaboration with Kellogg&#039;s Frosted Flakes and Tony the Tiger" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=13989" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=13989" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fkith-treat-kelloggs-frosted-flakes-cereal-tony-the-tiger-collaboration-collection-release-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1352	1136	UNDERCOVER Celebrates Its 35th Anniversary With a DMSG-Exclusive Capsule	undercover-celebrates-its-35th-anniversary-with-a-dmsg-exclusive-capsule	published	2025-12-11 09:10:31+00	3	17	\N	SummaryUNDERCOVER is celebrating its 35th anniversary with an exclusive event at Dover Street Market GinzaExclusive tees and bags are available to shop at the event, running from December 12-27, 20...	UNDERCOVER Celebrates Its 35th Anniversary With a DMSG-Exclusive Capsule	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fundercover-dover-street-market-ginza-35th-anniversary-capsule-release-info-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>SummaryUNDERCOVER is celebrating its 35th anniversary with an exclusive event at Dover Street Market GinzaExclusive tees and bags are available to shop at the event, running from December 12-27, 2025UNDERCOVER is celebrating its 35th anniversary with a special event and exclusive capsule collection launch at Dover Street Market Ginza (DSMG). The event is scheduled to run from December 12 - 27, turning the DSMG store into an immersive experience dedicated to the brand's world. The celebration highlights the legacy of designer Jun Takahashi, featuring the installation of iconic UNDERCOVER characters in the DSMG pilotis area and the display of 12 mannequins clad in the brand's Fall/Winter 2025 women's collection in the elephant space.Leading the event are special and limited-edition tees, featuring UNDERCOVER’s iconic blindfold bear graphics. These consist of long-sleeve and short-sleeve tees, available in black and white colorways with prices ranging from ¥16,500 - ¥28,600 JPY (approx. $106 - $184 USD).In addition to apparel, the release also offers exclusive bags, personally customized by Takahashi. Head over to UNDERCOVER's website and Instagram for more information. View this post on InstagramA post shared by UNDERCOVER (@undercover_lab)</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/undercover-dover-street-market-ginza-35th-anniversary-capsule-release-info" title="UNDERCOVER Celebrates Its 35th Anniversary With a DMSG-Exclusive Capsule" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.504+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.503+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.506+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.506+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2Fundercover-dover-street-market-ginza-35th-anniversary-capsule-release-info-0.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><ul><li>UNDERCOVER is celebrating its 35th anniversary with an exclusive event at Dover Street Market Ginza</li><li>Exclusive tees and bags are available to shop at the event, running from December 12-27, 2025</li></ul><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/undercover" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UNDERCOVER</a> is celebrating its 35th anniversary with a special event and exclusive capsule collection launch at <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/dover-street-market-ginza" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dover Street Market Ginza</a> (DSMG). The event is scheduled to run from December 12 - 27, turning the DSMG store into an immersive experience dedicated to the brand's world. The celebration highlights the legacy of designer Jun Takahashi, featuring the installation of iconic UNDERCOVER characters in the DSMG pilotis area and the display of 12 mannequins clad in the brand's Fall/Winter 2025 women's collection in the elephant space.</p><p>Leading the event are special and limited-edition tees, featuring UNDERCOVER’s iconic blindfold bear graphics. These consist of long-sleeve and short-sleeve tees, available in black and white colorways with prices ranging from ¥16,500 - ¥28,600 JPY (approx. $106 - $184 USD).</p><p>In addition to apparel, the release also offers exclusive bags, personally customized by Takahashi. Head over to UNDERCOVER's <a href="https://undercoverism.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">website</a> and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/undercover_lab/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a> for more information.</p><p><center><br /><blockquote class="instagram-media bypass" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/DSFPvrxkj-m/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:16px;"> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DSFPvrxkj-m/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style=" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><div style=" display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center;"><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;"></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;"></div></div></div><div style="padding: 19% 0;"></div><div style="display:block; height:50px; margin:0 auto 12px; width:50px;"><svg width="50px" height="50px" viewBox="0 0 60 60" version="1.1" xmlns="https://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="https://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><g transform="translate(-511.000000, -20.000000)" fill="#000000"><g><path d="M556.869,30.41 C554.814,30.41 553.148,32.076 553.148,34.131 C553.148,36.186 554.814,37.852 556.869,37.852 C558.924,37.852 560.59,36.186 560.59,3