1353	1137	WACKO MARIA Honors Ari Aster’s ‘Eddington’ With New Collection	wacko-maria-honors-ari-aster-s-eddington-with-new-collection	published	2025-12-11 06:58:14+00	3	17	\N	SummaryWACKO MARIA is releasing an eight-piece apparel capsule to commemorate Ari Aster's film, Eddington, in collaboration with A24The collection includes heavy weight T-shirts and crewnecks featu...	WACKO MARIA Honors Ari Aster’s ‘Eddington’ With New Collection	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2FFTAri-Aster-a24-Eddington-WACKO-MARIA-Collaboration-collection-Release-Info.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>SummaryWACKO MARIA is releasing an eight-piece apparel capsule to commemorate Ari Aster's film, Eddington, in collaboration with A24The collection includes heavy weight T-shirts and crewnecks featuring Joaquin Phoenix's character and his political ad quote: “LET’S FREE EACH OTHER’S HEARTS”The Eddington x WACKO MARIA collection drops today, December 12, via the WACKO MARIA webstore and PARADISE TOKYO storeWACKO MARIA is commemorating Ari Aster’s recent film Eddington with a collaborative collection.The eight-piece capsule comprises apparel, including washed heavy weight T-shirts and crew neck sweatshirts. A poster with co-lead star Joaquin Phoenix fronts a selection of heavy weight T-shirts and crew neck sweatshirts, along with embroidered Eddington and A24 logos on the top back. Meanwhile, his character’s political ad, which reads “LET’S FREE EACH OTHER’S HEARTS,” is printed on similar pieces. The same insignias are stitched on the back, but also sees an ad that reads “YOU WANNA LIVE IN SAN FRANCISCO? I DON’T THINK SO.”Check out the collab above. The Eddington x WACKO MARIA collection drops December 12 via the WACKO MARIA webstore and PARADISE TOKYO store.</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/ari-aster-a24-eddington-wacko-maria-collaboration-collection-release-info" title="WACKO MARIA Honors Ari Aster’s ‘Eddington’ With New Collection" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.517+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.517+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.519+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.519+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2FFTAri-Aster-a24-Eddington-WACKO-MARIA-Collaboration-collection-Release-Info.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><ul><li>WACKO MARIA is releasing an eight-piece apparel capsule to commemorate Ari Aster's film, <em>Eddington</em>, in collaboration with A24</li><li>The collection includes heavy weight T-shirts and crewnecks featuring Joaquin Phoenix's character and his political ad quote: “LET’S FREE EACH OTHER’S HEARTS”</li><li>The <em>Eddington</em> x WACKO MARIA collection drops today, December 12, via the WACKO MARIA webstore and PARADISE TOKYO store</li></ul><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/wacko-maria">WACKO MARIA</a> is commemorating <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/ari-aster">Ari Aster</a>’s recent film <a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/4/a24-eddington-official-trailer-stream-western-thriller-joaquin-phoenix-pedro-pascal-emma-stone-austin-butler-info"><em>Eddington</em></a> with a collaborative collection.</p><p>The eight-piece capsule comprises apparel, including washed heavy weight T-shirts and crew neck sweatshirts. A poster with co-lead star Joaquin Phoenix fronts a selection of heavy weight T-shirts and crew neck sweatshirts, along with embroidered <em>Eddington</em> and <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/a24">A24</a> logos on the top back. Meanwhile, his character’s political ad, which reads “LET’S FREE EACH OTHER’S HEARTS,” is printed on similar pieces. The same insignias are stitched on the back, but also sees an ad that reads “YOU WANNA LIVE IN SAN FRANCISCO? I DON’T THINK SO.”</p><p>Check out the collab above. The <em>Eddington</em> x WACKO MARIA collection drops December 12 via the WACKO MARIA webstore and PARADISE TOKYO store.</p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/ari-aster-a24-eddington-wacko-maria-collaboration-collection-release-info" title="WACKO MARIA Honors Ari Aster’s ‘Eddington’ With New Collection" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=53434" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=53434" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F11%2FFTAri-Aster-a24-Eddington-WACKO-MARIA-Collaboration-collection-Release-Info.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1354	1138	Drake's OVO Announces Upcoming Marvel Collaboration	drake-s-ovo-announces-upcoming-marvel-collaboration	published	2025-12-11 06:21:19+00	3	17	\N	SummaryDrake's OVO announced an exclusive collaboration with Marvel, set to drop this Friday, December 12, sparking intense album speculationThe collaboration is heavily linked to the X-Men hero Ic...	Drake's OVO Announces Upcoming Marvel Collaboration	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F09%2Fdrake-ovo-marvel-iceman-collaboration-announcement-000a.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>SummaryDrake's OVO announced an exclusive collaboration with Marvel, set to drop this Friday, December 12, sparking intense album speculationThe collaboration is heavily linked to the X-Men hero Iceman (Bobby Drake), which fans believe is the final thematic component of Drake's elaborate ICEMAN album rolloutThe merchandise drop signals the imminent release of the highly anticipated album, completing the year-long promotional campaign defined by cryptic messages and singlesUpdate:OVO is concluding the year with an exclusive collaboration with Marvel, launching tomorrow, December 12th. The collection leans into darker tones and heavy graphics, featuring major comic characters like Venom, Wolverine, Ghost Rider, and Doctor Doom. The artwork is intentionally gritty, looking authentically ripped from old comic book panels. Highlight pieces include a Venom hockey jersey and a flame-heavy Ghost Rider long-sleeve. With skate decks and accessories rounding out the capsule, the entire drop embraces winter layering and a raw, nocturnal aesthetic, available online and in OVO stores. View this post on InstagramA post shared by October&#39;s Very Own (@octobersveryown)Original Story: The countdown is on for a momentous convergence of hip-hop and comic book culture as Drake’s OVO prepares to drop an exclusive collaboration with Marvel this Friday, December 12. The announcement, made on OVO's Instagram Stories, has caught the attention of The Boy's fans all around the world. The timing of this highly anticipated apparel line has sparked frenzied speculation with the rumored focus being on none other than the iconic X-Men hero, Iceman (aka Robert Louis "Bobby" Drake) -- a potent symbolic link to the title of Drake’s long-teased upcoming album, ICEMAN.This OVO x Marvel capsule appears to be the final, chilling move in a strategic album rollout that has dominated 2025. Throughout the year, Drake has maintained the ICEMAN theme with cryptic social media messages, themed livestreams, and a string of promotional singles. This new clothing collection, merging the signature OVO aesthetic with the cool, monochromatic visuals of the mutant hero Bobby Drake, suggests the rapper is locking in the atmosphere before the full music project lands.The synergy is undeniable -- the hero known for his powerful, frozen exterior meeting the brand built on the sleek, cold style of Toronto's elite. If the past few months have been the slow, deliberate formation of ice, this Marvel collaboration acts as the final deep freeze. Fans are now speculating that the drop on December 12 is the ultimate confirmation that the ICEMAN album is finally set to hit streaming platforms.</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/drake-ovo-marvel-iceman-collaboration-announcement" title="Drake&#039;s OVO Announces Upcoming Marvel Collaboration" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.53+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.53+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.533+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.533+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F09%2Fdrake-ovo-marvel-iceman-collaboration-announcement-000a.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><ul><li><p data-path-to-node="0,0,0">Drake's OVO announced an exclusive collaboration with Marvel, set to drop this Friday, December 12, sparking intense album speculation</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="0,1,0">The collaboration is heavily linked to the X-Men hero Iceman (Bobby Drake), which fans believe is the final thematic component of Drake's elaborate <i>ICEMAN</i> album rollout</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="0,2,0">The merchandise drop signals the imminent release of the highly anticipated album, completing the year-long promotional campaign defined by cryptic messages and singles</p></li></ul><p><strong>Update:</strong></p><p>OVO is concluding the year with an exclusive collaboration with Marvel, launching tomorrow, December 12th. The collection leans into darker tones and heavy graphics, featuring major comic characters like Venom, Wolverine, Ghost Rider, and Doctor Doom. The artwork is intentionally gritty, looking authentically ripped from old comic book panels. Highlight pieces include a Venom hockey jersey and a flame-heavy Ghost Rider long-sleeve. With skate decks and accessories rounding out the capsule, the entire drop embraces winter layering and a raw, nocturnal aesthetic, available online and in OVO stores.</p><blockquote class="instagram-media bypass" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/DSFlKFajU6R/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:16px;"> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DSFlKFajU6R/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style=" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><div style=" display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center;"><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-g