v><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; height: 12.5px; transform: rotate(-45deg) translateX(3px) translateY(1px); width: 12.5px; flex-grow: 0; margin-right: 14px; margin-left: 2px;"></div><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; height: 12.5px; width: 12.5px; transform: translateX(9px) translateY(-18px);"></div></div><div style="margin-left: 8px;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 20px; width: 20px;"></div><div style=" width: 0; height: 0; border-top: 2px solid transparent; border-left: 6px solid #f4f4f4; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; transform: translateX(16px) translateY(-4px) rotate(30deg)"></div></div><div style="margin-left: auto;"><div style=" width: 0px; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-right: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(16px);"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; flex-grow: 0; height: 12px; width: 16px; transform: translateY(-4px);"></div><div style=" width: 0; height: 0; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-left: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(-4px) translateX(8px);"></div></div></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 24px;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 224px;"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 144px;"></div></div><p></a><p style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;"><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DSFlKFajU6R/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_blank" rel="noopener">A post shared by October&#39;s Very Own (@octobersveryown)</a></p></div></blockquote><hr /><p><strong>Original Story:</strong> The countdown is on for a momentous convergence of hip-hop and comic book culture as <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/drake">Drake</a>’s <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/ovo">OVO</a> prepares to drop an exclusive collaboration with <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/marvel">Marvel</a> this Friday, December 12. The announcement, made on OVO's Instagram Stories, has caught the attention of The Boy's fans all around the world. The timing of this highly anticipated apparel line has sparked frenzied speculation with the rumored focus being on none other than the iconic <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/x-men">X-Men</a> hero, Iceman (aka Robert Louis "Bobby" Drake) -- a potent symbolic link to the title of Drake’s long-teased upcoming album, <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/iceman"><em>ICEMAN</em></a>.</p><p>This OVO x Marvel capsule appears to be the final, chilling move in a strategic album rollout that has dominated 2025. Throughout the year, Drake has maintained the <em>ICEMAN</em> theme with cryptic social media messages, themed livestreams, and a string of promotional singles. This new clothing collection, merging the signature OVO aesthetic with the cool, monochromatic visuals of the mutant hero Bobby Drake, suggests the rapper is locking in the atmosphere before the full music project lands.</p><p>The synergy is undeniable -- the hero known for his powerful, frozen exterior meeting the brand built on the sleek, cold style of Toronto's elite. If the past few months have been the slow, deliberate formation of ice, this Marvel collaboration acts as the final deep freeze. Fans are now speculating that the drop on December 12 is the ultimate confirmation that the <em>ICEMAN</em> album is finally set to hit streaming platforms.</p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/drake-ovo-marvel-iceman-collaboration-announcement" title="Drake&#039;s OVO Announces Upcoming Marvel Collaboration" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=90183" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=90183" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F09%2Fdrake-ovo-marvel-iceman-collaboration-announcement-000a.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1355	1139	SR_A's Limited Release Capsule Is Centered Around Engineered Emotion	sr-a-s-limited-release-capsule-is-centered-around-engineered-emotion	published	2025-12-11 04:16:58+00	3	17	\N	SummarySamuel Ross's SR_A launched its debut eyewear collection featuring two limited-edition frames, TORQUE and ECLIPSE, hand-constructed from gold and silver foiled resinThe launch includes a new...	SR_A's Limited Release Capsule Is Centered Around Engineered Emotion	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F10%2Fsamuel-ross-sra-debut-eyewear-torque-eclipse-vintage-functional-athletic-pieces-limited-collection-release-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><div>SummarySamuel Ross's SR_A launched its debut eyewear collection featuring two limited-edition frames, TORQUE and ECLIPSE, hand-constructed from gold and silver foiled resinThe launch includes a new capsule of minimal leisure garments, specifically black and grey sweatpants and hoodie sets, built for vintage training and functional daily useRoss states the collection channels "movement and engineering" and embodies the SR_A studio's spirit, now available online and at select global retailersSamuel Ross’s SR_A has officially debuted its first-ever eyewear collection, introducing two distinct, limited-edition frames: TORQUE and ECLIPSE. Embodying the mantra "VIGILANCE. PRECISION.," the collection translates an emotional spirit of British engineering and freedom into wearable design.These striking frames blend sleek forms with bold, structured colors, realizing a contemporary culture deeply inspired by iconic British design principles. The eyewear is hand-constructed using intricate gold and silver foiled resin, lending each piece a sense of luxury and technical precision.Launching alongside the eyewear is a new capsule of vintage training and minimal leisure garments, built with functionality for rigorous daily use. This apparel drop includes essential black and grey sweatpants and hoodie sets, offering clean, purposeful silhouettes ready for everyday motion. This expansion reinforces Ross's unified design philosophy, which he describes as, "A feeling of the SR_A design studio; movement and engineering channeled through Custom vehicles, open-work watches, functional garments, and raw sporting equipment." The entire limited-edition capsule, representing an advanced intersection of industrial design and personal style, is available now at the online store and select global retailers.</div><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/samuel-ross-sra-debut-eyewear-torque-eclipse-vintage-functional-athletic-pieces-limited-collection-release-info" title="SR_A&#039;s Limited Release Capsule Is Centered Around Engineered Emotion" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p>	\N	2025-12-13 13:07:06.545+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.545+00	published	2025-12-13 13:07:06.548+00	2025-12-13 13:07:06.548+00	t	\N	<p><img width="620" src="https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F10%2Fsamuel-ross-sra-debut-eyewear-torque-eclipse-vintage-functional-athletic-pieces-limited-collection-release-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max" /></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><ul><li><p data-path-to-node="0,0,0">Samuel Ross's SR_A launched its debut eyewear collection featuring two limited-edition frames, TORQUE and ECLIPSE, hand-constructed from gold and silver foiled resin</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="0,1,0">The launch includes a new capsule of minimal leisure garments, specifically black and grey sweatpants and hoodie sets, built for vintage training and functional daily use</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="0,2,0">Ross states the collection channels "movement and engineering" and embodies the SR_A studio's spirit, now available online and at select global retailers</p></li></ul><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/samuel-ross">Samuel Ross</a>’s <a href="https://hypebeast.com/tags/sra">SR_A</a> has officially debuted its first-ever eyewear collection, introducing two distinct, limited-edition frames: TORQUE and ECLIPSE. Embodying the mantra "VIGILANCE. PRECISION.," the collection translates an emotional spirit of British engineering and freedom into wearable design.</p><p>These striking frames blend sleek forms with bold, structured colors, realizing a contemporary culture deeply inspired by iconic British design principles. The eyewear is hand-constructed using intricate gold and silver foiled resin, lending each piece a sense of luxury and technical precision.</p><p>Launching alongside the eyewear is a new capsule of vintage training and minimal leisure garments, built with functionality for rigorous daily use. This apparel drop includes essential black and grey sweatpants and hoodie sets, offering clean, purposeful silhouettes ready for everyday motion. This expansion reinforces Ross's unified design philosophy, which he describes as, "A feeling of the SR_A design studio; movement and engineering channeled through Custom vehicles, open-work watches, functional garments, and raw sporting equipment." The entire limited-edition capsule, representing an advanced intersection of industrial design and personal style, is available now at the <a href="http://SR-A.COM">online store</a> and select global retailers.</p><p><a href="https://hypebeast.com/2025/12/samuel-ross-sra-debut-eyewear-torque-eclipse-vintage-functional-athletic-pieces-limited-collection-release-info" title="SR_A&#039;s Limited Release Capsule Is Centered Around Engineered Emotion" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Click here to view full gallery at Hypebeast</a></p><p>    <a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=97961" target="_blank" rel="noopener">        <img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/1015938/Hypebeast_RSS_300x250_Rectangle&sz=300x250&c=97961" />    </a></p>	https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2025%2F12%2F10%2Fsamuel-ross-sra-debut-eyewear-torque-eclipse-vintage-functional-athletic-pieces-limited-collection-release-info-000.jpg?w=800&cbr=1&q=90&fit=max	0	f	f	f
1357	1080	В Петербурге задержали крупную партию немецкой муки из-за нарушений документов	v-peterburge-zaderzhali-krupnuyu-partiyu-nemeckoy-muki-iz-za-narusheniy-dokumentov	published	2025-12-12 14:31:55+00	2	17	\N	Почему в морском порту Петербурга не пустили муку из Германии – подробности инцидента	В Петербурге задержали крупную партию немецкой муки из-за нарушений документов	В морском порту Петербурга произошла необычная ситуация. Власти приняли решение не впускать крупную партию продукции. Причины связаны с отсутствием важных документов. Подробности выясняются.	\N	2025-12-13 13:08:22.652+00	2025-12-13 13:07:04.006+00	published	2025-12-13 13:08:22.657+00	2025-12-13 13:08:22.657+00	t	\N	<h2>Почему в морском порту Петербурга не пустили муку из Германии – подробности инцидента</h2>\n<p><strong>В морском порту Петербурга произошла необычная ситуация. Власти приняли решение не впускать крупную партию продукции. Причины связаны с отсутствием важных документов. Подробности выясняются.</strong></p>\n<figure><img src="https://spbdnevnik.ru/uploads/block/image/1134897/__medium_495928afd7e74bb84e85784f2f69801d.jpg.jpg" alt="В Петербурге задержали крупную партию немецкой муки из-за нарушений документов" /><figcaption>Фото: Роман Пименов / «Петербургский дневник»</figcaption></figure>\n<div><p>Как сообщает <a href="https://spbdnevnik.ru/news/2025-12-12/v-peterburg-ne-propustili-725-kilogramm-pshenichnoy-muki-iz-germanii">Петербургский дневник</a>, в одном из портов города была остановлена поставка пшеничной муки, прибывшей из Германии. Общий вес задержанной продукции составил 725 килограмм. Причиной для запрета на ввоз стала нехватка информации о проведенных лабораторных исследованиях, которые должны были подтвердить безопасность товара для потребителей.</p><p>В ходе проверки выяснилось, что в предоставленных документах отсутствуют сведения о тестах на наличие вредителей и загрязнений. Эти данные являются обязательными для ввоза подобной продукции на территорию России. Без них невозможно удостовериться, что мука не представляет угрозы для хранения и дальнейшего использования.</p><p>Сотрудники Россельхознадзора приняли решение не допускать муку на внутренний рынок. Ведомство подчеркивает, что подобные меры необходимы для предотвращения распространения вредителей, которые могут нанести ущерб запасам зерна и другим сельскохозяйственным продуктам.</p><p>В последнее время контроль за импортом продуктов питания в Петербурге заметно ужесточился. Власти уделяют особое внимание качеству и безопасности товаров, поступающих из-за рубежа. Это связано с ростом числа случаев выявления нарушений при ввозе различных партий продукции.</p><p>Пока неизвестно, будет ли возвращена задержанная партия в страну-отправитель или утилизирована на территории России. Представители контролирующих органов отмечают, что подобные ситуации возникают регулярно, и напоминают импортерам о необходимости строго соблюдать все требования к оформлению документов и проведению лабораторных испытаний.</p></div>	https://spbdnevnik.ru/uploads/block/image/1134897/__medium_495928afd7e74bb84e85784f2f69801d.jpg.jpg	1	f	f	f
